@node "what it is" "What it is"
Grabby is a very simple screen grabber for screens displayed over a Retina graphic board.

Features:

- grab every 1-8 or 24 bit screen displayed over Retina

- save in IFF format

Restrictions:

- can not grab 16 bit screens 

- can only save in IFF format

- must be started form shell
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
Grabby requires at least AmigaOS2.0 and a Retina graphic board and its libraries.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
Just copy the executable in your search path.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
Just type "grabby filename [delay]" in a shell. "filename" is the name and path where Grabby will save the pic , "delay" is an optional delay in seconds Grabby will wait before doing its job. You can use this time to switch to another screen . Grabby will always grab the FrontScreen.
@endnode

@node "Copyright" "Copyright"
